event.title: Google Duo Download
event.description:
Google Duo is a simple, fast one-to-one video calling app for everyone—whether you’re on Android or iOS, a fast or slow connection, in New York or New Delhi. Like Allo, Duo is based on your phone number, allowing you to reach anyone in your phonebook. And its simple interface fades away when you’re in a call, so it’s just the two of you.

The search engine behemoth, Google has ultimately launched a new Video Calling application called Duo at it prestigious Google I/O Event 2016 held in New Delhi and a couple of weeks backs. During the on-going event, Google has rolled out a new video calling app by showcasing the amazing benefits of this new video calling application. Along with the new Duo video calling app, Google also unveiled a new messenger app called Allo that lets its users make a chat conversation with their friends and beloved ones.
